    <h1>Radha Krishna</h1><br><br>
    <h2 class="featurette-heading fw-normal lh-1">The Eternal and divine Love story of Devi Radha and Shri Krishna.
        <span class="text-body-secondary"></span></h2>
    <p class="lead">
    Even though the love between Radha and Krishna has influenced many followers, the narratives and interpretations might
    vary based on traditions and cultural influences. Being an incarnation of lord Vishnu, Krishna was born as the son of
    Vasudeva and Devaki. But lord Krishna was secretly raised in the village of Gokul by his foster parents, Nanda and
    Yashoda. However, Radha is said to be a cowherd girl in a place called Vrindavan. Since childhood, she has been devoted
    towards lord Krishna. She is known for her selfless love towards lord Krishna.
    
    As Krishna grows older, he realizes his divine personality and charming personality. He used to enchant everyone around
    him by playing the flute magnificently. He is believed to be the magnitude of love. They have grown together and played
    together cheerfully. Even though Krishna's charming personality attracted many girls, Radha’s divine and intense love
    was the key factor that drew Krishna to her. They didn't end up together because Krishna left Vrindavan and Radha to
    accomplish his divine mission. What made this story extraordinary is the devotion of Radha towards Krishna that made her
    wait throughout her life.
    
    The cheerful divine interactions have made the Radha Krishna story more delightful. The love between them is considered
    a significant form of devotion and is remembered through poems, arts, etc., in Hinduism. Their story is presented in
    ‘Bhagvata Purana’, a sacred Hindu text. The divine love of Radha and Krishna is depicted as ‘Ras Leela’.
    </p>
</div>
</div>
