<div class="row featurette">
    <div class="col-md-7">
        <p class="lead">As mentioned before, lord Krishna was the incarnation or an avatar of lord Vishnu. He was born to fulfil some
        responsibilities on earth. The divine purpose behind his actions is to restore righteousness and guide humanity. His
        relationships and interactions on earth, including Radha are relieved to be a spiritual lesson to convey a profound
        truth. Signifying the different aspects of divinity, it is said that lord Krishna is married to 16,108 wives such as
        Rukmini and Satybhama.
        
        Being a symbolic reflection of divine love and devotion, the story of Radha and Krishna is beyond a conventional marital
        union.

        Even though the Radha Krishna love story is believed and be an inspiration by many people, there is a great debate and
        interpretations over Radha’s marital status. Some narratives depict the marriage of Radha to Ayan, arranged by her
        family.
        
        However, in other interpretations, it is said that lord Krishna allowed Radha to marry Ayan as a divine Leela without
        losing the existing deep spiritual connection with her.
        
        At the same time, some narratives didn't agree with her marriage due to her wholesome devotion and spiritual union with
        lord Krishna.As said before, Radha is known for her unconditional love and devotion towards Lord Krishna. Her thoughts of suppressing
        her willingness and ego for the happiness of Krishna exemplify the significance of sacrifice and selflessness in an
        individual’s relationship and devotion.

        Radha’s faith towards Krishna is unbreakable like a big rock. Her divine trust towards lord Krishna, even when he was
        far away teaches us the role and importance of faith in a relationship while facing enormous challenges.
        </p>
    </div>
